1. Execute smoke testing for VCST environment. 
2. Clear cache, clear local storage in browser
3. Read get_variables_env.js
4. Sign in as a FRONT_ADMIN via standart form
5. Execute smoke testing. Use file Frontend.TestSuit.xml
6. For Admin site/Back office scenariors open a second tab and go to BACK_URL
7. Open Dev tools F12 > console and keep it open
8. After any action fetch errors (include JavaScript errors) in console and print it out
9. Make a logout after testing. Click on User name in the upper right corner in the top header, and click the icon Logout
10. Create a report after each section (ID, Title, Result, Detailed error)
11. If the bugs were found create a bug report with Test case ID


